<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REMOVAL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The rear oil seal can be serviced in chassis. The procedure is performed as part of engine
                        overhaul and separately, when required.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>In-Chassis Procedure</title>
            <para>Perform the following steps
                <emph type="bold"></emph>(
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050705">7.5</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two (2) flywheel mounting bolts located at the 3 and 9 o'clock positions. Install
                    two (2) guide dowel pins
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4375</emph>
                    at these locations.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove remaining ten (10) flywheel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide flywheel out of the flywheel housing and off guide dowel pins.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>With flywheel removed, guide dowel pins can be removed from crankshaft flange.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Checking Flywheel Housing Bore Concentricity And Face Runout</title>
            <para>Perform the following steps
                <emph type="bold">(Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050706">7.6</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Flywheel housing bore concentricity and flywheel housing face runout is checked to ensure
                        proper engine to transmission alignment.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check flywheel housing bore concentricity as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Attach a dial indicator to the crankshaft and place the indicator tip against the
                        flywheel housing bore.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft slowly and record the total indicator variation. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>
                        for housing bore to concentricity tolerance.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050705" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3039" filename="../figeg3/eg3039.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.5.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Flywheel Housing</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Flywheel</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Dowel Pins</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. Flywheel Mounting Bolts (12)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050706" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2376" filename="../figeg2/eg2376.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.6.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Dial Indicator</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Crankshaft Flange</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Flywheel Housing</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check flywheel housing face runout as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Attach a dial indicator to crankshaft and place indicator tip against flywheel
                        housing bore. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e105_133.xml" xrefid="ef1050707">7.7</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Measure at four points, 90&#176; apart for total face variation.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <important>
                            <para>KEEP THE CRANKSHAFT END PLAY AT ZERO IN THE SAME DIRECTION FOR ALL MEASUREMENTS.
                            </para>
                        </important>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>
                        for flywheel housing face runout tolerance.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
